 definitions + guitar-specific notes + examples. Covering scale degrees, chords, progressions, and practical techniques."/><meta name="google-adsense-account" content="ca-pub-9662479821167655"/><link rel="canonical" href="https://www.ototheory.com/resources/glossary"/><link rel="alternate" hrefLang="en" href="https://www.ototheory.com/resources/glossary"/><link rel="alternate" hrefLang="ja-JP" href="https://www.ototheory.com/ja/resources/glossary"/><link rel="alternate" hrefLang="x-default" href="https://www.ototheory.com/resources/glossary"/><meta property="og:title" content="Guitar Glossary – Quick Music Theory Terms"/><meta property="og:description" content="Quick reference glossary with guitar-focused definitions and practical examples."/><meta name="twitter:card" content="summary"/><meta name="twitter:title" content="Guitar Glossary – Quick Music Theory Terms"/><meta name="twitter:description" content="Quick reference glossary with guitar-focused definitions and practical examples."/><link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico?favicon.0b3bf435.ico" sizes="256x256" type="image/x-icon"/><link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" sizes="any"/><link rel="icon" href="/favicon-32x32.png" sizes="32x32" type="image/png"/><link rel="icon" href="/favicon-16x16.png" sizes="16x16" type="image/png"/><link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/apple-touch-icon.png" sizes="180x180" type="image/png"/><script src="/_next/static/chunks/a6dad97d9634a72d.js" noModule=""></script></head><body class="geist_a71539c9-module__T19VSG__variable geist_mono_8d43a2aa-module__8Li5zG__variable antialiased"><div hidden=""><!--$--><!--/$--></div><noscript><iframe src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/ns.html?id=GTM-NXSC7TN2" height="0" width="0" style="display:none;visibility:hidden"></iframe></noscript><header class="border-b border-black/10 dark:border-white/10"><div class="container flex items-center justify-between h-24"><a class="flex items-center gap-2" href="/"><img alt="OtoTheory" width="280" height="84" dec